docs/TEST_GATES.md:157:The action registry must preserve explicit safety classification. Machine-readable inventory output must remain parseable JSON and must not execute actions. Read-only cockpit commands must not execute destructive Git, release, tag, merge, cleanup, or remote operations. `cockpit run` may execute registered `read_only` actions through argument-vector execution. Bounded actions may be listed as action metadata, but they must be blocked unless an explicit bounded-action allow path is used. Destructive actions must remain blocked.
docs/TEST_GATES.md:253:## Communication artifact garbage collector
docs/TEST_GATES.md:255:`./ns artifact-gc` reports transient communication artifacts without deleting them. `./ns artifact-gc --execute` removes only registered transient `.agentic/commands/current.yaml` and `.agentic/commands/current.sh` compatibility files. It must not delete `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`, because that file is part of the committed terminal-evidence pointer chain.
docs/planning/V0.3.8_SCOPE.md:32:- improved documentation for the `request -> run -> review -> cleanup` loop;
docs/planning/GUI_COCKPIT_EXPANSION_ROADMAP.md:79:The GUI may show branch, dirty state, open PRs, release checks, tag state, and CI status. Merge, tag, release, cleanup, and remote mutation actions should stay outside default GUI execution until explicitly designed and tested.
docs/planning/GUI_COCKPIT_EXPANSION_ROADMAP.md:95:- No release, merge, tag, cleanup, or force-push buttons.
docs/architecture/LOCAL_COCKPIT_FOUNDATION.md:13:The v0.3.14 foundation introduced a shared action inventory and a central cockpit status command. The v0.3.15 action layer adds explicit execution for registered `read_only` actions while keeping bounded actions blocked unless explicitly allowed and destructive actions blocked. It does not execute destructive git, release, or cleanup actions.
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:1:# Communication Artifact Garbage Collector
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:5:Communication, handoff, terminal, and command-run artifacts must not accumulate without classification. They also must not be removed by ad-hoc shell deletion. The project therefore uses a central artifact registry in `.agentic/communication_artifacts.yaml` and a deterministic garbage-collector workflow.
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:9:The goal is deterministic technical quality, not quick cleanup. A cleanup that risks deleting pending commands, evidence, handoff state, terminal logs, or pointers is a product defect.
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:14:- default to dry-run for cleanup candidates;
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:17:- never delete `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`; repair it if needed;
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:19:- write a cleanup report before any mutating cleanup;
docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:24:The registry covers the existing temporary and communication artifact classes currently used by the repository: `/tmp/agentic-project-kit-*.log`, `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`, `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`, `docs/reports/command_runs/*.md`, `.agentic/commands/inbox/*`, and `.agentic/commands/current.*`.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
docs/workflow/HANDOFF_STATE.md:34:## Communication artifact cleanup rule
docs/workflow/HANDOFF_STATE.md:36:Temporary communication files must be centrally classified before cleanup. Use `.agentic/communication_artifacts.yaml` as the allowlist and policy source. Do not use ad-hoc `rm` on `docs/reports`, `.agentic/commands`, handoff files, terminal logs, command-run reports, or pointer files. A garbage collector must start with dry-run behavior and must write a cleanup report before any deletion.
docs/workflow/HANDOFF_STATE.md:40:Temporary communication artifacts must be centrally recognizable and removable only through registered safe paths. Use `./ns artifact-gc` for a dry-run plan and `./ns artifact-gc --execute` only after reviewing the plan. The collector must not delete arbitrary `docs/reports` files, release evidence, handoff state, source files, or unregistered paths.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:11:- `UPLOADED`: performs bounded cleanup of the temporary evidence branch.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:49:UPLOADED -> cleanup temporary evidence branch -> IDLE
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:50:FAILED -> preserve evidence; no automatic cleanup
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:55:This means routine work uses an explicit request followed by the same command for validation and cleanup:
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:62:After `UPLOADED`, run `agentic-kit workflow cleanup` or `python3 tools/next-step.py` once more for cleanup. Then reply in chat with `done` or `d`.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:152:- `./ns fail`: upload preserved FAILED-state evidence without cleanup or retry.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:197:agentic-kit workflow cleanup
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:226:- `UPLOADED`: evidence was uploaded; inspect it, then run `agentic-kit workflow cleanup`.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:227:- `FAILED`: run `agentic-kit workflow fail-report` when bounded local evidence exists, then stop and inspect evidence before cleanup or retry.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:235:- `workflow cleanup`: cleans an UPLOADED/CLEANUP evidence branch, otherwise no-ops with a status message.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:236:- `workflow fail-report`: from FAILED, uploads preserved bounded evidence for diagnosis without cleanup or retry.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:265:- `FAILED`: local task failed or timed out; evidence is preserved when possible and no automatic cleanup is performed.
docs/WORKFLOW_OUTPUT_CYCLE.md:291:After the `IDLE` step succeeds, the state becomes `UPLOADED`. The LLM can inspect the remote temporary evidence branch. A later `agentic-kit workflow cleanup` call cleans up and returns to `IDLE`.
